headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown had 21 points and eight assists, Semi Ojeleye added 18 points and the Boston Celtics rolled to an 124-97 win over the Orlando Magic on Friday night in their return to action following an virus-related week-long hiatus.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics run past Magic 124-97 after week-long hiatus

events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Andre Drummond tied his career high with 33 points and grabbed 23 rebounds, and Cedi Osman scored 25 points in leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 106-103 win over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Drummond has 33 points, 23 boards as Cavs top Knicks 106-103

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo overcame poor free-throw shooting to score 31 points, Khris Middleton hit two late 3-pointers and the Milwaukee Bucks held off the Dallas Mavericks 112-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks survive shaky free-throw shooting to edge Mavs 112-109

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored a career-high 33 points to help Oklahoma City beat the Chicago Bulls and former Thunder coach Billy Donovan 127-125 in overtime Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander's 33 lead Thunder past Bulls in OT

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell made six 3-pointers on his way to 26 points and the Utah Jazz used a 21-0 second-half run to power past the Atlanta Hawks 116-92 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 26, Jazz use 21-0 run to beat Hawks 116-92

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 21 points, 11 assists and eight rebounds, and Anthony Davis added 17 points against his former team in the Los Angeles Lakers' fifth consecutive victory, 112-95 over the New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron, Davis lead Lakers' 112-95 dismantling of Pelicans

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard had 27 points and six assists in three quarters, Paul George scored 26 and the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers manhandled the Sacramento Kings 138-100 on Friday night.
